 Fractaliseur is a small program which aims to compute the Mandelbrot
 set and save the result in a raw 24bits image. You can use Gimp to
 open it for instance. There are two implementations : a CPU-based
 computation written in C and a NVIDIA GPU-based computation written in
 CUDA.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
 Making instructions: for the CUDA implementation, type "make gpu" and
 for the CPU-based one, "make cpu". You can compile the both by typing
 "make" or "make all".
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
 Usage: after making the program, just type "./fraccpu" or "./fracgpu".
 It will create a file named "test.data" which contains the 24bits
 image.
 
 Thanks for trying, enjoy !
